    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Poor People And Criminality</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Diane Pagen letter disputes April 15 letter responding to article about crime rate and birth control</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The writer of ''The Crime Rate and Birth Control'' (letter, April 15) implies that the poor bear children who become criminals, so it is consequently good to give them birth control or abortions. Her comments are pro-eugenics thinking, and she is misinformed as well.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The writer of ''The Crime Rate and Birth Control'' (letter, April 15) implies that the poor bear children who become criminals, so it is consequently good to give them birth control or abortions. Her comments are pro-eugenics thinking, and she is misinformed as well.</p>
        <p>Poor people are not more prone to criminality from birth; they only face greater hardship that might lead to committing a crime.</p>
        <p>Diane Pagen  Bedford Park, the Bronx</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
